// ADD these fields to your EXISTING Institute model — don't recreate the
// whole model, just add these lines:
//
//   model Institute {
//     ...
//     logoUrl           String?  // uploaded logo, shown top-left on receipts
//     signatureUrl      String?  // optional — scanned/photographed signature image
//     signatoryName     String?  // e.g. "Ravi Kumar, Director" — printed under the signature line
//     nextReceiptNumber Int      @default(1)  // see note below on why this exists
//   }

// ADD this field to your EXISTING Payment model:
//
//   model Payment {
//     ...
//     receiptNumber String? @unique
//   }
//
// Why nextReceiptNumber lives on Institute rather than being computed
// on the fly: a receipt number needs to be STABLE — reprinting the same
// receipt next week must show the same number, and numbers should be
// sequential without gaps for basic bookkeeping sanity. Storing a
// running counter per institute and incrementing it atomically inside
// the same transaction that creates the Payment is what guarantees that,
// even if two payments get recorded at the exact same moment.
